 :tx/rationale "FORMAL INSIGHT: The task management UX gap IS a coherence gap in the formal framework. Phi_SP (spec-impl boundary divergence) measures gaps between what's specified and what's implemented. But there's an UNSTATED boundary: the Phi_UX between what the SYSTEM KNOWS (store has 278 tasks with rich attributes) and what the AGENT CAN ACCESS (truncated titles, no search, no filtering). This is a new instance of REFLEXIVE DIVERGENCE (spec/22-reflexive.md): the system's CAPABILITY MODEL claims rich task management, but the system's INTERFACE provides only primitive listing. The store IS the source of truth — but truth locked behind Datalog queries is truth that agents cannot easily access. FORMALLY: Let U(S) be the usable information from store S via the CLI interface. Let T(S) be the total information in S. The USABILITY RATIO u(S) = |U(S)| / |T(S)| should approach 1.0 as the interface matures. Currently u(S) for task management is approximately 0.3 — agents can access ~30% of task information without raw queries. Fixing task display (pyramid), search, and filtering pushes u(S) toward 0.8+. This is the operational analogue of the bilateral forward scan: does the interface satisfy the specification?"
